The Oyo State Police Command on Tuesday said it has arrested officers who allegedly shot a student of the Polytechnic of Ibadan, Samuel Akinsuyi. The command said the officers are currently undergoing orderly room trial. The State Police Public Relations Officer, Adewale Osifeso, who stated this on Tuesday said the commissioner of police, Ngozi Onadeko, has ordered full-scale investigations into the events that led to the unfortunate shooting of Samuel Akinsuyi along Eruwa-Ibadan road on March 11, 2022.  